---
import SiteLayout from "../components/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Tayyub Yaqoob — AI analytics systems, publications, and evidence"
  description="UK-based senior digital analyst focused on AI analytics systems, technical publications, recognition, and evidence-backed technical credibility."
  pathname="/"
  footerTitle="Request the evidence pack."
  footerLead="For senior roles, consulting, recommendation context, publication requests, or a closer look at the supporting material behind the case studies."
>
  <style slot="head">
    .press-cell{padding:22px 16px;min-height:104px;gap:10px;align-items:center;text-align:center}
    .press-cell .pn-fallback{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;height:34px;line-height:1;letter-spacing:-.02em;font-weight:800;font-size:18px}
    .press-cell .pk{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9.5px;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-top:2px}
    .brand-bbc .pn-fallback{font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-weight:900;color:#000;letter-spacing:-1px}
    .brand-bbc .pn-fallback b{background:#000;color:#fff;padding:5px 6px;margin-right:2px;font-size:15px;display:inline-block;line-height:1}
    .brand-bbc .pn-fallback b:last-child{margin-right:0}
    .brand-tesco .pn-fallback{color:#ee1c2e;font-family:Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-style:italic;font-weight:800;font-size:24px;letter-spacing:-.03em;position:relative;display:inline-flex;padding-bottom:3px}
    .brand-tesco .pn-fallback::after{content:"";position:absolute;left:0;right:0;bottom:0;height:2px;background:#0064b1;border-radius:1px}
    .brand-gm .pn-fallback{color:#0046ad;font-family:Inter,sans-serif;font-weight:800;font-size:17px;letter-spacing:-.02em}
    .brand-royal-london .pn-fallback{color:#1d3a6e;font-family:Georgia,serif;font-weight:600;font-size:18px;letter-spacing:.01em}
    .brand-nerdwallet .pn-fallback{color:#008a05;font-family:Inter,sans-serif;font-weight:800;font-size:18px;letter-spacing:-.01em}
    .metrics-strip{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:14px;margin-top:18px}
    .metric{background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--r-md);padding:18px 20px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:4px;transition:transform .25s,border-color .25s,box-shadow .25s}
    .metric:hover{transform:translateY(-2px);border-color:var(--line-2);box-shadow:var(--shadow-1)}
    .metric .v{font-family:var(--serif);font-size:34px;letter-spacing:-.02em;line-height:1;color:var(--ink)}
    .metric .v em{font-style:italic;color:var(--terra)}
    .metric .k{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10.5px;letter-spacing:.04em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted)}
    .metric .sub{font-size:12.5px;color:var(--ink-2);line-height:1.4;margin-top:2px}
    @media (max-width:880px){.metrics-strip{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}}
  </style>

  <section class="hero wrap" data-screen-label="01 Intro" id="top">
    <div class="hero-grid">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow rv" data-parallax="6">
          <span class="dot"></span>
          Senior Digital Analyst · 8 Million Stories · Stirling, UK
        </div>
        <h1 class="rv d1">
          I build <span class="grad">AI analytics</span> systems with a clear <span class="marked">evidence path</span>.
        </h1>
        <p class="lede rv d2">
          Production analytics systems, technical publications, supporting recognition, and a public evidence route designed for serious review. The goal of this site is not to sound impressive. It is to make the case <b>inspectable</b>.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-cta rv d3">
          <a href="/evidence" class="btn btn-primary" data-magnet>Open the evidence →</a>
          <a href="/case-studies" class="btn btn-ghost" data-magnet>See case studies ↗</a>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-pills rv d4">
          <a class="hero-pill" href="/publications">Live article URLs</a>
          <a class="hero-pill" href="/recognition">Recognition context</a>
          <a class="hero-pill" href="/testimonials">Testimonials</a>
          <a class="hero-pill" href="/about">Profile page</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-card rv d2">
        <img src="/assets/portrait.jpeg" alt="Tayyub Yaqoob" />
        <div class="hero-card-cap">
          <div>
            <b>Tayyub Yaqoob</b>
            <span>Evidence-first portfolio</span>
          </div>
          <span>2026</span>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-evidence left compact">
          <div class="hev"><span class="ic terra">01</span><b>Case studies</b></div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-evidence right compact">
          <div class="hev"><span class="ic sage">02</span><b>Evidence</b></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section wrap first" data-screen-label="Clients">
    <div class="sec-head rv">
      <div class="sec-head-l">
        <span class="sec-tag"><span class="dot" style="background:var(--terra)"></span>§ Client exposure</span>
        <h2>Work delivered into <em>real environments</em>.</h2>
        <p>Where disclosure is permitted, the client base helps explain the level of operational trust behind the systems work.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sec-head-r">/ selected examples</div>
    </div>

    <div class="press-strip rv">
      <div class="press-cell brand-bbc"><span class="pn-fallback"><b>B</b><b>B</b><b>C</b></span><span class="pk">Media · UK</span></div>
      <div class="press-cell brand-tesco"><span class="pn-fallback">Tesco</span><span class="pk">Financial · UK</span></div>
      <div class="press-cell brand-gm"><span class="pn-fallback">General Mills</span><span class="pk">Consumer · global</span></div>
      <div class="press-cell brand-royal-london"><span class="pn-fallback">Royal London</span><span class="pk">Insurance · UK</span></div>
      <div class="press-cell brand-nerdwallet"><span class="pn-fallback">NerdWallet</span><span class="pk">Personal finance</span></div>
    </div>

    <div class="metrics-strip rv">
      <div class="metric"><span class="v">35<em>+</em></span><span class="k">Technical articles</span><span class="sub">Live URLs plus archive continuity where publisher structure changed.</span></div>
      <div class="metric"><span class="v"><em>3</em></span><span class="k">IGI Global reviews</span><span class="sub">Publisher-led peer-review activity on file.</span></div>
      <div class="metric"><span class="v"><em>50+</em></span><span class="k">Teams on internal systems</span><span class="sub">Operational trust across recurring workflows.</span></div>
      <div class="metric"><span class="v">12<em>+</em></span><span class="k">AI / ML credentials</span><span class="sub">Google, AWS, LinkedIn Learning, and related training.</span></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section wrap" id="proof" data-screen-label="02 Proof">
    <div class="sec-head rv">
      <div class="sec-head-l">
        <span class="sec-tag"><span class="dot" style="background:var(--terra)"></span>§ Site structure</span>
        <h2>What this site is <em>for</em>.</h2>
        <p>The structure now follows how a reviewer actually evaluates technical credibility: case studies, publications, recognition, evidence, and only then the supporting layers.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sec-head-r">/ reviewer-first</div>
    </div>

    <div class="bento">
      <a class="cap feature rv" href="/evidence">
        <span class="cap-num">/ 01 — Evidence</span>
        <div class="cap-icon"><svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6"><path d="M7 4 H17 A2 2 0 0 1 19 6 V18 A2 2 0 0 1 17 20 H7 A2 2 0 0 1 5 18 V6 A2 2 0 0 1 7 4 Z"/><path d="M8 9 H16"/><path d="M8 13 H16"/><path d="M8 17 H13"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Evidence <em>before claims</em>.</h3>
        <p>Role, systems, publications, recognition, public code, and archival continuity are now grouped in one primary route instead of being buried in the footer.</p>
        <span class="cap-go">Open evidence →</span>
      </a>
      <a class="cap rv d1 t-ochre" href="/case-studies">
        <span class="cap-num">/ 02</span>
        <div class="cap-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6"><circle cx="6" cy="6" r="2.2"/><circle cx="18" cy="6" r="2.2"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2.2"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Production <em>case studies</em>.</h3>
        <span class="cap-go">Case studies →</span>
      </a>
      <a class="cap rv d2 t-coral" href="/publications">
        <span class="cap-num">/ 03</span>
        <div class="cap-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6"><rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="16" rx="2"/><line x1="3" y1="9" x2="21" y2="9"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Live articles and <em>archive record</em>.</h3>
        <span class="cap-go">Publications →</span>
      </a>
      <a class="cap rv t-rust" href="/recognition">
        <span class="cap-num">/ 04</span>
        <div class="cap-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6"><path d="M12 3 L20 7 V13 C20 17 16.5 20.5 12 22 C7.5 20.5 4 17 4 13 V7 Z"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Recognition and <em>peer review</em>.</h3>
        <span class="cap-go">Recognition →</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section wrap" id="featured" data-screen-label="03 Selected work">
    <div class="sec-head rv">
      <div class="sec-head-l">
        <span class="sec-tag"><span class="dot" style="background:var(--ochre)"></span>§ Production work</span>
        <h2>Flagship <em>systems</em>.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="sec-head-r"><a href="/case-studies">All case studies →</a></div>
    </div>

    <div class="feat-strip">
      <a class="feat-card rv" href="/case-studies" data-tilt>
        <div class="feat-card-viz">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 400 240" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
            <defs><linearGradient id="fc1" x1="0" x2="1"><stop offset="0" stop-color="#c44d2c" stop-opacity=".15"/><stop offset="1" stop-color="#c89942" stop-opacity=".05"/></linearGradient></defs>
            <rect width="400" height="240" fill="url(#fc1)"/>
            <path d="M20 200 L80 160 L140 170 L200 120 L260 130 L320 80 L380 60" stroke="#c44d2c" stroke-width="2" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="feat-card-body">
          <span class="feat-card-tag">/ 01 — Forecasting</span>
          <h4>Forecasting and traffic planning workflows</h4>
          <p>Recurring forecasting workflows used to support planning and variance detection.</p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a class="feat-card rv d1" href="/case-studies" data-tilt>
        <div class="feat-card-viz">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 400 240" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
            <rect width="400" height="240" fill="#fff"/>
            <path d="M50 160 A110 110 0 0 1 350 160" fill="none" stroke="#e8e2d2" stroke-width="16"/>
            <path d="M50 160 A110 110 0 0 1 350 160" fill="none" stroke="#d97757" stroke-width="16"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="feat-card-body">
          <span class="feat-card-tag">/ 02 — Monitoring</span>
          <h4>Sentiment and topic monitoring</h4>
          <p>LLM-assisted monitoring kept subordinate to analyst judgment and proof quality.</p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a class="feat-card rv d2" href="/case-studies" data-tilt>
        <div class="feat-card-viz">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 400 240" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
            <rect width="400" height="240" fill="#fff"/>
            <rect x="34" y="50" width="120" height="58" rx="10" fill="#fff5d7" stroke="#c89942"/>
            <rect x="244" y="50" width="120" height="58" rx="10" fill="#fde8df" stroke="#c44d2c"/>
            <rect x="140" y="138" width="120" height="58" rx="10" fill="#e6ecd9" stroke="#7a8f5e"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="feat-card-body">
          <span class="feat-card-tag">/ 03 — Search visibility</span>
          <h4>AI-mention and visibility tracking</h4>
          <p>Evidence-oriented workflows for AI-facing and conventional search surfaces.</p>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section wrap" id="evidence" data-screen-label="04 Contact">
    <div class="ev-card rv">
      <div class="ev-card-l">
        <span class="sec-tag" style="margin-bottom:12px"><span class="dot" style="background:var(--terra)"></span>§ Request support material</span>
        <h2>Need the <em>supporting pack</em>?</h2>
        <p>The site now keeps public proof, archive continuity, and supporting evidence cleaner, but some of the strongest material still sits behind approval, confidentiality, or direct request. Ask if you need the closer file.</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" data-magnet>Request evidence pack →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="ev-card-r">
        <ul class="ev-list">
          <li><span class="ev-ic">01</span>Role and recommendation context</li>
          <li><span class="ev-ic">02</span>Case-study support material</li>
          <li><span class="ev-ic">03</span>Publication archive asset</li>
          <li><span class="ev-ic">04</span>Peer-review and recognition context</li>
          <li><span class="ev-ic">05</span>Public code references</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
